    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yet not through struggling could frail man"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The secret of this myst’ry find;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Nor chance, by stumbling, come upon"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Such hidden things—to these he’s blind."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Behold in heav’n a throne is set,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And One upon the throne revealed;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And held in His right hand a scroll—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The mystery is tightly sealed."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Through all the universe, a cry—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "’Can one be found of such great worth"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The scroll to take?’ ... yet no reply,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "From heav’n, below, or on the earth."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Were it a matter now for man"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "By chance, or some ability,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Then surely one would now step forth"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To open God’s economy."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yet sad and solemn was that sight."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "John wept as then he looked around;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And we, too, still might weeping be"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "If none at all were worthy found."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But then the angel said, ’Weep not!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Behold, the Lion has prevailed"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To take the scroll and loose its seals;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He has the mystery now unveiled!’"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "7"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "So, John looked up the Lion to see,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But, lo, he then beheld a Lamb;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Christ both o’ercame the enemy,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And wrought redemption’s work for man."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "8"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The angels fall before His throne,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Four living creatures offer praise,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "All glory to the Lion-Lamb;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Let us with theirs our voices raise!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "9"
    }
